**Logical Thinking**
The current TreeNode and the current target sum can identify a state uniquely.
```
		           state(node, targetSum)
				/          \
state(node.left, targetSum - node.val)  state(node.right, targetSum - node.val)
```
We keep track of the `path` on the fly.
Our final state is `state(leaf, x)`. If `x` turned out to be `0`, we add `path` to `result`. Else, we simply backtrack.
